DTSTAMP:20260710T074012Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260923
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260924
SUMMARY:Deadline: Horizon Europe Cluster 2: Culture\, Creativity and Inclus
 ive Society (HORIZON-CL2-2026-01-HERITAGE) — incl. AI and Creative Conte
 nt topic
DESCRIPTION:Horizon Europe Cluster 2 funds research on culture\, creativity
 \, and inclusive society. The 2026 call (HORIZON-CL2-2026-01-HERITAGE\, la
 unched May 12\, 2026) covers 7 topics with an indicative budget of €85.5
  million. Topic HERITAGE-04 is explicitly titled 'Towards a fair and trans
 parent market for cultural and creative content in the era of generative A
 I\,' covering: impacts of generative AI on creative industries employment\
 ; upskilling needs for creative workers\; policy and regulatory frameworks
 \; fair remuneration and transparency. Highly relevant for research into A
 I and cultural/creative industries\, artists' rights in the AI era\, and s
 ociotechnical studies of AI and culture. ELIGIBILITY: consortium-based app
 lications (minimum 3 organisations from 3 different EU/associated countrie
 s are typical for Horizon RIA grants\; check call conditions on the Fundin
 g & Tenders portal for specific requirements). Deadline: 23 September 2026
 . Apply via the EU Funding & Tenders portal (ec.europa.eu/info/funding-ten
 ders).\n\nOrganisation: European Research Executive Agency (REA) / Europea
 n Commission\, Horizon Europe\nLocation: European Union and associated cou
 ntries. Consortium-based\; typically requires partners from multiple EU/Ho
 rizon member states.\nAward: Indicative total budget €85.5 million acros
 s 7 topics (2026 call). Individual project amounts vary by topic. Up to 10
 0% funding rate for non-profit research organizations. No application fee.
 \nDuration: Typically 3-4 years\; varies by topic.\n\nMore: https://rea.ec
 .europa.eu/funding-and-grants/horizon-europe-cluster-2-culture-creativity-
 and-inclusive-society/european-cultural-heritage-and-cultural-and-creative
 -industries_en?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://rea.ec.europa.eu/funding-and-grants/horizon-europe-cluster-2-cu
 lture-creativity-and-inclusive-society/european-cultural-heritage-and-cult
 ural-and-creative-industries_en?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_
 medium=referral
LOCATION:European Union and associated countries. Consortium-based\; typica
 lly requires partners from multiple EU/Horizon member states.
END:VEVENT
